A circular, doubly-linked list that supports constant time operations only (except for the iterator, of course).

Author:
Rosario Raulin

append

public void append(DLinkedList<T> other)
Appends the other list to this one. Its guaranteed runtime is O(1).

Note: This method destroys other in that it changes it's internal structure. This way we can guarantee constant runtime.

Parameters:
other - the list to be appended to this one
